cd : changes directory
ls : lists files in the directory
        -l : gives a long list
        -t : gives a list sorted by modifiied time
        -a : show hidden files also
        -u : gives list sorted by name
less    : displays text file
mkdir : makes directory
rm : removes file 
      -r : removes recursively.
      -f : force remove
history : lists all commands
sudo    : executes command as a superuser
	su - : takes u to the root 
chown : changes ownership of a file
       usage :sudo chown owner:group filename 
chmod   : change file mode
	usage : sudo chmod 777 filename
useradd : adds new user to a system
          usage : useradd -Ggroupname username(creates newuser and adds him t a                                                 group)
groupadd : adds new group
usrmod : adds existing user to a group
        usage : usermod -Ggroupname username
history  : lists previous commands(starts from most latest)
